        "subtitle": "A Secret Glue That Makes You Want to Stay Close — Your Body Saying This Person Is Part of Your Team",
        "simple": "Inside your brain there is a special friendship juice called oxytocin. When you hug someone you love or hold a puppy, your brain squirts this juice into your body to make you feel warm and safe. It is like a secret glue that makes you want to stay close to your family and friends. This chemical pull is what helps moms take care of babies and friends stay loyal to each other. Without this juice we would not feel the pull to protect and love the people around us.",
