        "simple": "Gravity is the ultimate invisible pull that affects everything that has weight. It is what keeps your feet on the floor and keeps the moon from floating away into deep space. Every single person has a tiny bit of gravity too. Even though we are too small to feel it, we are all pulling on each other just by existing. Gravity teaches us that the bigger something is, the more it pulls things toward it. In life, big ideas and big love have a gravity that draws people in just like a planet.",
