        "simple": "Your brain has special copycat cells called mirror neurons. When you see someone smile, these cells fire in your brain as if you were the one smiling. This is why you feel sad when you see a character cry in a movie. These cells act like an invisible bridge that connects your feelings to everyone else's feelings. This pull makes us want to be kind and help others because in a way we are feeling what they feel.",
